CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F401A1781619075
OL,3,CRow over potential cull of endangered
OL,4,Chill ponies on Dartmoor
OL,6,FNatural England is including Dartmoor
OL,7,Fhill ponies in livestock counts under
OL,8,Fits new moorland agri-environmental
OL,9,Fschemes that provide payments for
OL,10,Ffarmers for grazing upland in ways
OL,11,Fthat benefit nature.
OL,13,FCampaigners warn the new schemes will
OL,14,Fcut livestock, including ponies, by
OL,15,F56% to 89%, even though they say
OL,16,Fprevious cuts to stocking densities `
OL,17,Fwhich the ponies were previously
OL,18,Fprotected from ` have not boosted
OL,19,Fbiodiversity on Dartmoor.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,402,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F401A1781619075
OL,3,CRow over potential cull of endangered
OL,4,Chill ponies on Dartmoor
OL,6,FThe Dartmoor Hill Pony Association
OL,7,Fsays the move will force commoners,
OL,8,Fwho have rights to put livestock on
OL,9,Fthe commons of the moor, to choose
OL,10,Fbetween commercial sheep and cattle
OL,11,Fand the ponies for which they have
OL,12,Ftraditionally been guardians.
OL,14,FThe loss of ponies would be damaging
OL,15,Ffor the biodiversity of the landscape,
OL,16,Fas they are the best grazer of the
OL,17,F"monoculture" Molinia grass that has
OL,18,Fcome to dominate the moor, Joss Hibbs,
OL,19,Fsecretary of the DHPA which represents
OL,20,Fcommoners who keep the ponies, said.
OL,26,@yD@AOUyD@MO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,402,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F401A1781619075
OL,3,CRow over potential cull of endangered
OL,4,Chill ponies on Dartmoor
OL,6,FMs Hibbs said: "We are in a situation
OL,7,Fif Natural England pushes their
OL,8,Fapproach through of this number cut
OL,9,Fand bringing the ponies in, the impact
OL,10,Fon the ponies will be greater than it
OL,11,Fis on livestock because they will lose
OL,12,Fthat competition.
OL,14,F"We know, therefore, Natural England's
OL,15,Fapproach will devastate the Dartmoor
OL,16,Fhill pony population, it will make
OL,17,Ffarms financially unviable and it's
OL,18,Fextremely doubtful there will be any
OL,19,Fenvironmental benefit."
OL,26,@nD@POUvD@AOU{D@WO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,402,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F401A1781619075
OL,3,CRow over potential cull of endangered
OL,4,Chill ponies on Dartmoor
OL,6,FShe warned that if commoners chose
OL,7,Fcommercial livestock to earn a living,
OL,8,Fthe ponies would be lost ` and if they
OL,9,Fchose the ponies they would become
OL,10,Funviable and the farms would go, which
OL,11,Fwould in turn lead to the loss of the
OL,12,Fponies which are safeguarded by the
OL,13,Ffarmers.
OL,15,FCampaigners said the contracts could
OL,16,Fcome into force as early as the end of
OL,17,Fthis year, meaning the majority of
OL,18,Fponies rounded up in annual "drifts"
OL,19,Fin October would not be returned to
OL,20,Fthe moor ` with the most likely
OL,21,Foutcome being a cull.
OL,26,@zD@]OUzD@dO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
